│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs due to a strict assertion in SCEVExpanderCleaner::cleanup that all users of inserted  │
│ instructions must themselves be inserted during SCEV expansion. Even after purging non-inserted instructions in │
│ the SCEV and memory check blocks, some users outside those blocks may still reference inserted instructions,    │
│ causing the assert to fire. To make cleanup robust, I will relax the assertion by converting it into a          │
│ debug-only check that doesn't abort: it will only assert for instruction users and skip non-instruction users,  │
│ preventing the hard failure while still aiding debugging builds.                                                │
